The paper deals with linear regression with norm and sparsity constraints, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of convex and combinatorial optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the optimization (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Finally, the joint use of norm and sparsity constraints may have implications for signal processing (cs.SI).
